online or alternate format for the remainder of the spring semester. The University plans to complete the semester on its current schedule.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daily Post Staff |title=UOG classes going online for semester |url=https://www.postguam.com/news/local/uog-classes-going-online-for-semester/article_ab6c7f7c-6f27-11ea-a365-bb1c1b15e4c4.html |website=The Guam Daily Post |publisher=The Guam Daily Post |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn Saturday, March 28, [[President of the United States|United States President]] [[Donald Trump]] approved a disaster declaration for Guam that orders Federal assistance to supplement territory and local coronavirus recovery efforts.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefings-statements/president-donald-j-trump-approves-guam-disaster-declaration-3/|title=President Donald J. Trump Approves Guam Disaster Declaration|website=The White House|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> The President also signed the national $2 trillion COVID-19 relief bill with approximately $111 million allocated to Guam.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://dphss.guam.gov/2019-novel-coronavirus-2019-n-cov/ Coronavirus information] from [[Guam Department of Public Health and Social Services]]\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Guam|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in insular areas of the United States|Guam]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Oceania|Guam]]\n[[Category:Health in Guam]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United States|coronavirus pandemic]]\n\n\n{{Guam-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTimeline:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Guam"}
